 suicide note, Naik accused three people, including Arnab, of non-payment of dues as a reason cited for committing suicide, but Arnab was granted interim bail from the Supreme Court of India on 11 November 2020. 7. Television Rating Manipulation Case Mumbai Police started an inquiry against the potential manipulation of selected TRP points. They received a complaint against these activities, and they started their inquiry on that basis. In a complaint, the name of several people cropped up, like Partho Das Gupta, former CEO of the Broadcast Audience Research Councill. Police accused Das broadcasted fake viewership ratings to cheat advertisers. Such allegations were levelled against Republic, more specifically against Arnab. Mumbai Police confiscated the phone and several chats communicated between Arnab and Partho Das Gupta. Police included Whatsapp messaging service in their charge sheet. These chats were leaked to the public that showed a close connection between Arnab and Partho Das Gupta, indicating TRP manipulation. Gupta and Arnab were subjected to severe criticism and condemnation for their malice practices after the messages were leaked into the public domain. News Broadcaster of India demanded suspension of Republic Media network from Indian Broadcasting Foundation citing leaked messages. Several legal actions were demanded against Arnab Goswami. Information on Glance Full name: Arnab Ranjan Goswami Occupation: News Journalists, anchor Physical Measurements and Statistics Height: In feet inches-5'11'' In meters- 1.80m In centimetres: 180cm Hair colour: Black Eye Colour: Black Personal Life of Arnab Goswami Place of Birth: Guwahati Birth Date: 9 October 1973 Nationality: Indian Zodiac Sign: Libra School: Mount St. Mary's School, Delhi Cantonment, Kendriya Vidyalaya, Jabalpur Cantonment University: Hindu College, University of Delhi, and Oxford University, England Education bio-data: Graduation in Sociology, Masters in Social Anthropology Religion: Hinduism C