up are Educationist Ramakanta and Ramdas Pai and his wife. All of them have invested through SARG Media Holding Private Limited. Arnab purchased a major portion of shares held by Rajeev Chandrasekhar and his company, Asianet News Media and Entertainment. Goswami reached the total ownership and, in a statement issued by them, it is said that Arnab holds 82% shares of Republic TV. The company holds 99% equity in digital infrastructure. Editor's Guild Resignation Episode In a live television show, Arnab announced his resignation from the Editor Guild in the wake of the Palghar Mob Lynching. Arnab levelled accusations against Shekhar Gupta that he is compromising on journalism for not speaking against this issue. Maharashtra Power Minister Nitin Raut made a complaint, and Nagpur Police filed a First Information Report against Arnab Goswami. The FIR filed against Goswami included charges like promoting enmity between two groups on religion or race, provocation with intent to cause a riot, and other sections of the Indian Penal Code. Being an Author Arnab wrote a book called Combating Terrorism: The Legal Challenge in 2002. Nature of Journalism His journalism has always been criticized, and questions have been levelled against his partial nature of reporting. Experts in journalism have opinionated that he favours the ruling Bhartiya Janta Party on many occasions and situations. Critics have pointed out that he avoids criticism of the ruling party and always presents opposition in the poor limelight. Goswami is also known that he has popularised the two terms: Anti-National and Urban Naxal. These terms he uses for those who criticize the right-wing ideology. It is alleged that he tries to evoke hyper-nationalism and jingoism in the audience. His news channel is like North Korean media, which tries to muzzle dissent and has a close affinity toward the state. Controversial Events 1. Tharoor Defamation Case Shashi Tharoor, an Indian Parliamentarian, on 26 May 2017, lodged a civil defamation suit against Arnab and his media network in the Delhi High court. Arnab, in his show, claimed that Tharoor had a role in the Sunanda Pushkar case. Judges of the High court came down very heavily on the media group. 2. Statements Over Keralites A 30-second clip was circulating on social media in 2018 where he called a group "the most shameless bunch of Indians I have ever seen". He was discussing the foreign aid for flood-hit Kerala state. Later it was revealed that these remarks were not for the people of Kerala but the "Tukde- Tukde Gang" leftist people. 3. News Broadcasting Standards Authority (NBSA) Case NBSA of India asked for a full-screen apology on 30 August 2018 from the Republic Tv network for using foul language against a group of people at a political rally and harassing one of his journalists. They removed the video clip and account from YouTube. They did not comply with the NBSA order and filed an appeal in court. NBSA again asked Republic media in October 2019 for a public apology after the media network resisted complying in the matter of Arnab accused of standard prohibitions on racial and religious stereotyping violations. He did not follow the order. 4. Palghar Mob Lynching Numerous FIR was registered against Arnab Goswami in connection with the Palghar Mob Lynching case, and he was accused of spreading misinformation and using inflammatory language. 5. Uddhav Thackeray vs Arnab Goswami A taxi driver and 2 republic tv journalists were arrested from the farmhouse of Maharashtra Chief Minister Uddhav Thackeray on trespassing charges. The issue became a confrontation point between Arnab Goswami and Uddhav Thackeray's Government. His group demanded the immediate release of his journalist from the Government. They also made allegations that the Shiv Sena threatened him with the Channel Republic Bharat and Republic TV blackout. 6. Suicide Case Police detained Arnab Goswami on the charges of abetment of suicide of Anvay Naik on 4 November 